 head of the Carnegie Endowment for International Peace, Butler promoted the Kellogg-Briand Pact outlawing aggressive war and in 1931 shared the Nobel Peace Prize with Jane Addams. He advised seven presidents on international affairs.","number":4},{"category":"character","header":"Theodore Roosevelt called him Nicholas Miraculous","body":"A lifelong Republican insider and friend of Theodore Roosevelt, Butler earned the nickname Nicholas Miraculous for his prodigious energy and connections. In 1912 he received the electoral votes meant for Vice President James Sherman, who died days before the election.","number":5}],"burial":{"cemetery_name":"Cedar Lawn Cemetery","city":"Paterson","county":"Passaic","state":"New Jersey","country":"United States"},"education":[{"school_name":"Columbia College","type":"undergraduate","dates":"1882","notes":"A.B. 1882; A.M. 1883; Ph.D. 1884."}],"career":[{"role":"President","organization":"Columbia University","start_year":1902,"end_year":1945},{"role":"President","organization":"Carnegie Endowment for International Peace","start_year":1925,"end_year":1945}],"slug":"nicholas-butler-1862"},"HD2272":{"id":"HD2272","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":9,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00721","mother_id":"HD2270"},"tags":[],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1895,"month":7,"city":"Bergen Point","state":"New Jersey"},"death":{"year":1947,"month":2,"city":"England","state":"England"},"gender":"female","marriages":[{"spouse_id":"X01552","children_ids":[],"marriage_number":1},{"spouse_id":"I01611","children_ids":[],"marriage_number":1}],"number_of_marriages":2,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Sarah Schuyler Butler","first_name":"Sarah","middle_name":"Schuyler","maiden_name":"Butler","married_names":[],"photo_url":"https://res.cloudinary.com/dc5clrqtw/image/upload/v1780860893/55887553_09415461-3e6a-426f-b0a0-a68425c3274e_ewykmn.jpg","bio_blurb":"Republican organizer; daughter of Nicholas Murray Butler"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"category":"politics","header":"She organized Republican women in New York","body":"A daughter of Columbia's president Nicholas Murray Butler, Sarah became vice-chairman of the New York Republican State Committee and a prominent organizer of women voters in the 1920s. She was among the most visible Republican women of her generation.","number":1},{"category":"marriage","header":"She married into a British baronetcy","body":"In 1933 Sarah married Captain Henry Walter Neville Lawrence, a Coldstream Guards officer and son of Sir Walter Roper Lawrence, first Baronet. She spent her later years in England and is buried in a Surrey churchyard.","number":2}],"slug":"sarah-butler-1895"},"HD2271":{"id":"HD2271","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":8,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"X00720","mother_id":"HD2265"},"tags":["banker"],"sources":[],"birth":{"year":1865,"month":5,"day":23,"city":"Jersey City","state":"New Jersey","country":"United States"},"death":{"year":1905,"month":1,"day":4,"country":"United States"},"gender":"male","notable":{"is_notable":true,"notable_category":["business"],"primary_url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Edwards_Ogden_Schuyler","notable_blurb":"New York stockbroker and exchange member"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I01610","children_ids":[],"marriage_number":1}],"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"disp